<2ND_LINE>BC-Senate Trade Roll Call,400</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 61-37 roll call Wednesday by which
the Senate failed to override President Reagan's veto of the trade
bill.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to override the
president's veto while a ``no'' vote was a vote to support the veto.
   A two-thirds majority ``yes'' vote by the 98 senators who were
voting on the bill was required to override the president's veto
and thus put the bill into law over his objections. Because a
two-thirds majority ``yes'' vote was not obtained, Reagan's veto
was sustained and the bill thus died.
   Voting yes were 51 Democrats and 10 Republicans.
   Voting no were 2 Democrats and 35 Republicans.
