<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--HotelFire     06-09 0155</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Hotel Fire,0158</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Guests Evacuated In Vegas Highrise Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAS VEGAS, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Guests evacuated the downtown 34-story
Fitzgeralds Casino-Hotel after a carelessly discarded cigarette
ignited a pile of linen on the 24th floor, officials said.
   There were no injuries among the hotel's occupants, who
evacuated without incident shortly after noon Wednesday, but one
firefighter was hurt when a high-pressure hose snapped and struck
his head.
   A hotel employee discovered the blaze shortly after noon, and
fought it with a hand-held extinguisher until firefighters arrived,
said Evert Wilson, a fire department spokesman.
   Wilson said the fire began in a service elevator area when
someone discarded a cigarette onto the linen, but the fire never
got hot enough to activate the resort's automatic sprinklers.
   Hotel spokesman Fred Kosik said 98 percent of the hotel's 655
rooms were rented, but he didn't know how many people were actually
in the hotel, the state's tallest building.
</TEXT>
