<HEAD>Kitty Dukakis Checks Out of Hospital</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kitty Dukakis was released from the hospital
today, six days after delicate spinal surgery. She was accompanied
by her husband, Michael Dukakis, who clinched the Democratic
presidential nomination Tuesday night.
   Mrs. Dukakis, wearing a neck brace, said that she always knew
that Massachusetts General Hospital was ``the greatest hospital in
the world, and now I know why.''
   Her husband the Massachusetts governor, made no comment. He was
to accompany her to their home before returning to work at the
Statehouse.
   Mrs. Dukakis, 51, was in visible pain, but spent several minutes
thanking the doctors, nurses and hospital staff who treated her.
   She will have to wear a neck brace for several weeks, but said
her doctors told her she could take it off at the Democratic
National Convention in July on the night her husband formally
accepts the nomination.
   Mrs. Dukakis said Wednesday she was no longer experiencing the
numbness and pain she suffered for several weeks prior to the
operation to replace two herniated discs in her neck. But she said
her hip was very painful. Doctors removed bone slivers from her
left hip to replace the discs.
   ``It hurts, but I've been walking a lot,'' she said in a
telephone interview. ``I'm going to practice some stairs in a
little while.''
   Dukakis gained a mathematical lock on the nomination Tuesday
with victories in the final four primaries.
