<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Germany-Defect     06-09 0140</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Germany-Defect,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>East German Official Defects In West Germany</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An East German trade official based in
West Germany has defected along with his wife and son, a West
German government official said Thursday.
   The official, who spoke to The Associated Press on condition of
anonymity, confirmed that 42-year-old Klaus Gruetzmacher, who was
employed by the East Germans as a trade expert in Duesseldorf, had
defected.
   The official also confirmed details of the defection contained
in a report by the mass-circulation Bild tabloid. The Bild report,
which is to appear in newspaper's Friday editions, was telexed in
advance to other news media.
   Bild said Gruetzmacher's wife, Hannelore, who worked for an East
German trucking company in Hamburg, and his son Jens, a member of
the East Berlin Comic Opera, had also defected to the West.
</TEXT>
