<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Australia-Fire     06-09 0112</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Australia-Fire,0115</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hundreds Evacuate Burning Airport Terminal In Australia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire swept through the domestic
passenger terminal at Sydney's airport early Thursday, but no
injuries were reported.
   The fire caused severe damage to a first-class lounge, the
terminal's roof and a baggage check-in area and forced hundreds of
workers and passengers to flee the building, a spokesman for
Australian Airlines said.
   The blaze started in an air-conditioning duct and caused
millions of dollars in damage, said the spokesman, who spoke on
condition of anonymity.
   Flights were delayed for up to three hours by the blaze and
eight were canceled. The cause of the fire was being investigated.
</TEXT>
