close to the shore. Fermin Reyes, Mrs. Reyes' husband, told police
the skier refused to move when Reyes tried to warn him away.
   His wife panicked when the skier came within six inches of her
raft, and she began paddling toward shore. She collapsed in a few
inches of water and died shortly afterward. An autopsy revealed the
cause of death as a cardiac arrhythmia brought on by fright, said
Gwinnett County Coroner Randy Simpson.
