<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People-Jessica     06-09 0183</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Jessica,0188</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Toddler Rescued From Well Faces Wrestler In Benefit For Ill Child</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LANCASTER, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   First it was baseball, now wrestling for
Midland toddler Jessica McClure as she helps raise money for an ill
youngster.
   Jessica will go into the ring Saturday with World Class
Wrestling star Kevin Von Erich to raise money for 5-year-old
Brennan Bolin, who awaits a heart-lung transplant, said fund-raiser
organizer Bonnie Arnold.
   Jessica, whose 58 hours trapped in a Midland well last October
drew international attention, also took part in a fund-raising
balloon release for Brennan on March 31.
   A few days later, she threw out the first pitch for the American
League home opener of the Texas Rangers.
   ``At the beginning of the event for fun he (Von Erich) will be
tumbling around with Jessica,'' Mrs. Arnold said Thursday. ``We're
not going to let him hurt her, or her hurt him either. It's a fun
bout.''
   Brennan needs $125,000 for his operation, said Mrs. Arnold. The
fund drive so far has raised about $55,000. The Bolins and the
McClures are acquaintances, said Mrs. Arnold.
