<2ND_LINE>AM-Kitty Dukakis,230</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mrs. Dukakis Heads Home From Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kitty Dukakis, the wife of likely Democratic
presidential nominee Michael Dukakis, went home from the hospital
Thursday to further recover from delicate spinal surgery.
   Her husband made sure the ride home was comfortable, positioning
a pillow behind his wife's neck as they drove away from
Massachusetts General Hospital in Boston toward their home in
suburban Brookline.
   She made several jokes about her inability to turn her head
because of a neck brace she must wear for several weeks.
   ``The one promise that my doctors have made is that the night
Michael accepts the nomination I can take this collar off,'' Mrs.
Dukakis said. That will come at the Democratic National Convention
in mid-July.
   Asked when she would resume campaigning for her husband, Mrs.
Dukakis smiled and said:
   ``The doctors and nurses are right here and my husband is to my
right so I have to tell you that I promised them that I will not
get back on the campaign trail until the convention.''
   Mrs. Dukakis, 51, began experiencing pain and numbness several
weeks ago, and a preliminary diagnosis indicated two herniated
discs in her neck. She underwent surgery six days ago.
   Two bone fragments were taken from Mrs. Dukakis' hip and fused
to the ruptured discs. Because of that procedure, Mrs. Dukakis is
expected to walk with a limp for several weeks.
</TEXT>
