<2ND_LINE>AM-Crops-Oranges,110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Orange Forecast Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The nation's orange harvest for the 1987-88
crop year is estimated at 201 million boxes, 1 percent above last
month's forecast and 10 percent over the level of a year ago, the
Agriculture Department said Thursday.
   The Florida crop, based on June 1 indications, was estimated at
nearly 141 million boxes, unchanged from last month but a 17
percent jump from last season, the report said.
   California production was forecast at 31.8 million boxes, an
increase of 3 percent over May but down 8 percent from the 1986-87
level. The Arizona crop was expected to total 2.3 million boxes, 27
percent below last season.
   The report said that Texas orange production was about 1.43
million boxes, compared with 875,000 boxes harvested last season.
