<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Britain-Clowes     06-09 0298</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Britain-Clowes,0307</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Investigators Shut Down Barlowe Clowes Securities Firms</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Financial investigators closed two Barlowe Clowes
securities management companies that handled $325 million invested
by 7,000 people, news reports said Thursday.
   The Times of London said Peter Clowes, chairman of the parent
company, refused to disclose the whereabouts of $249 million
investors put into Barlowe Clowes International based in Gibraltar.
   Investors of the other closed company, Britain-based Barlow
Clowes Gilt Managers, will get their money back, said Malcolm
London of accountants Cork Gully.
   Specific allegations against the companies were not announced,
but the Department of Trade and Industry began investigating the
two firms last November ``after concern about Barlow Clowes Gilt
Managers,'' Channel 4 said.
   It said action speeded up when the newly established,
government-sponsored Securities Investment Board began to operate
in London's City financial district on April 29.
   It said the board acted May 23 to stop Barlow Clowes Gilt
Managers taking on more business and two days later dealings in the
parent company, James Ferguson, were suspended.
   ``A winding up order against Barlow Clowes Gilt Managers was
obtained on May 27 and on June 7, Barlow Clowes International in
Gibraltar was closed down,'' the report said.
   Channel 4 said Clowes' lawyers in a statement Thursday night
said he was not going to be elusive and was working with them to
find a solution to the problem.
   The Gibraltar company specialized in managing government bonds
known as gilts, from gilt-edged securities, so known because
interest and repayment are guaranteed.
   The Times said Clowes came from the northern city of Manchester
and was associated with a range of bank accounts in London,
Gibraltar, Geneva and elsewhere and was a director of more than 20
companies operating in jewelry, computers, real estate management
and mailing services.
</TEXT>
