<TEXT>
   The stock market hovered around Wednesday's
closing levels today, pausing near its highest levels of the year.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, up 48.36 points on
Wednesday, dropped back .18 to 2,102.77 by noontime today. on Wall
Street.
   Gainers outnumbered losers by about 8 to 7 in the overall tally
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 720 up, 631 down and
466 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 122.90 million shares at
noontime, down from 169.70 million at the same point Wednesday.
   A large part of that activity was concentrated in a single issue
_ Detroit Edison, which was steady at 14 amid a flurry of large
blocks keyed to the company's impending quarterly dividend.
   But otherwise, analysts said signs persisted of increased
enthusiasm for stocks among money managers at investing
institutions.
   Until late last month, fears of rising interest rates and
inflation prompted those professionals to keep large amounts of
their assets out of the stock market.
   But with interest-rate fears having cooled and stocks up sharply
in the past week and a half, analysts said money managers might
feel mounting pressure to make heavier commitments to stocks in
time for their midyear reports to clients.
   Pannill Knitting climbed 2{ to 9}. Late Wednesday Sara Lee Corp.
said it would make a $10-a-share tender offer for 50 percent of
Pannill.
   Infinity Broadcasting jumped 8] to 29~ in the over-the-counter
market. A management group offered to acquire the company for $30 a
share.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks
slipped .03 to 152.83. At the American Stock Exchange, the market
value index was up 1.19 at 307.42.
