<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks,0185</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Share Prices Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices on the London Stock Exchange rose
Thursday, boosted by technical factors and the upward momentum on
Wall Street Wednesday.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
ended 13.3 points, or 0.72 percent, higher at 1,841.5.
   The Dow Jones industrial average was down 0.89 point at 2,101.87
at the close of the London session. However, traders said London
equities were still inspired by Wednesday's 48.36-point gain to
2,102.95 and a positive finish to stock index futures in New York
on Wednesday.
   The jump higher in London was ``a belated recognition on the
move Wednesday on Wall Street,'' said Nicholas Knight, an equity
strategist with James Capel and Co. in London.
   ``There's an understanding in the market that we're approaching
post-crash highs, so no one wants to pile in unless there's
certainty that we'll take out those post-crash highs,'' Knight said.
   A spate of expectedly good results failed to stimulate buying,
and there was little other news to generate excitement for most of
the day.
</TEXT>
