<HEAD>Cray Research Tops List Of Profitable Electronics Companies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cray Research Inc., the world's biggest maker of
supercomputers, was the nation's most profitable electronics
company in 1987 for a second consecutive year, according to a
magazine survey released Thursday.
   Minneapolis-based Cray posted a net profit equaling 21.4 percent
of its revenue, Electronic Business magazine said. The rankings are
for publicly held companies that get at least 70 percent of their
sales from electronics.
   Here are the top 10 profit makers, with their names, hometowns,
net profit as a percentage of revenue in 1987, and revenue,
according to Electronic Business:
   1. Cray Research Inc., Minneapolis, 21.4 percent, $687.3 million.
