<HEAD>Dean Witter Restructures Division</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dean Witter Reynolds Inc. said it is
restructuring its fixed-income operations, but a spokesman declined
Thursday to comment on claims that the move is resulting in layoffs.
   The investment firm said in a statement that in addition to
concentrating on government and corporate securities trading, it
will increase the amount of capital committed to its high-yield
debt and asset-backed securities trading unit.
   Spokesman Paul Marrone said managers involved in the
restructured units will decide whether to add or to lay off
employees. ``There have been no announcements'' on layoffs, he said.
   But a source within the firm on Thursday said people were being
laid off, although he could not provide a specific number. The
executive agreed to discuss the matter only if not identified by
name.
   There were reports on Wall Street that 50 to 100 people were
being laid off.
