<HEAD>New Electric Company Formed by Citizens Energy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Michael Kennedy, president of Citizens Energy
Corp., a non-profit energy company, announced Thursday the
formation of a new subsidiary, Citizens Power and Light Corp.
   The new corporation is a wholesale electric utility in the
business of purchasing and marketing electric power in the United
States and certain international markets, Kennedy said in a release.
   It joins Citizens Energy, originally formed by Kennedy's
brother, U.S. Rep. Joseph P. Kennedy II, as a low-cost alternative
for consumers.
   ``We have demonstrated our ability to package and deliver
creative, economic solutions to utility supply needs, and at the
same time assist low-income consumers with the burden of energy
costs,'' said Michael Kennedy, son of the late Robert F. Kennedy.
   ``The incorporation of Citizens Power and Electric represents a
corporate commitment to the major expansion of our electric
business,'' he said.
   Larry M. Kellerman, formerly of Portland General Electric, has
been named president of the new company.
