<1ST_LINE>u f AM-Japan-Markets 1stLd-Writethru   06-09 0111</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets, 1st Ld-Writethru,0115</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Stocks, Dollar Lower</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates thruout with morning closings. No Pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices lost ground in active trading Friday
on the Tokyo Stock Exchange, while the U.S. dollar moved lower
against the Japanese yen.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, the Tokyo
market's most closely-followed index, fell 50.42 points, or 0.18
percent, to finish the morning session at 28,021.60.
   The index had closed at a record high 28,072.02 points Thursday.
   Meanwhile, the dollar was trading at 124.87 yen by late morning,
down 0.56 yen from Thursday's closing level. It had slumped as low
as 124.60 yen earlier the session before rebounding.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
